  "design_principles": [
    "Frostvale is the northern glacial wall; passes and mining mountains (Lostfeld) leak pressure into the central basins.",
    "Twin Cities and Eresteron form the contested heart: fertile river plains between badlands, mountains, and east-coast trade.",
    "Eldoria sits northwest of the heartland, framed by forest (Faerwood) and the Gilgeth cordillera.",
    "Gilgeth and Lostfeld are mountain screens: they separate Groth and Vilefin from the league cities while gating access to Faerwood.",
    "Faerwood (west) and Glenwood (southeast) are discontinuous old-growth: separated by arid, urban, and coastal buffers.",
    "Tidefall rules the warm eastern gulf; Dreadwind Isles are the same naval sphere. Dur Khadur is the arid trade hinge between Vilefin, Groth, Glenwood, and the sea."
  ],
